article.headline: Wichita St 82, Drake 77
article.story: WICHITA, Kan. (AP) -- Sean Ogirri scored a career-high 29 points Wednesday night to lead Wichita State past Drake 82-77. Ogirri hit five 3-pointers and had two three-point plays as the Shockers built an 18-point lead in the second half. Kyle Wilson added 14 for Wichita State (13-8, 4-6 Missouri Valley Conference) and Ryan Martin added 11. The Shockers were up by 15 with 5 minutes to go when Drake (11-10, 2-8) rallied to cut the lead to two with only a minute to go. The Shockers led 69-51 with 7:45 to go in the second half before Drake began chipping away. Still trailing by 15 with 5:03 to go, Drake ralled to cut the deficit to two at 77-75 with just over a minute left. Wichita State pulled away at the free throw line for the final margin. All five Drake players scored in double figures, led by Aliou Keita and Josh Young with 15 points each. Nick Grant had 14 points, Ajay Calvin had 11 and Al Stewart added 10 for the Bulldogs.
